## Quick Test: The 80-Character Rule

Find a paragraph in your work. Count the characters in the longest line. Over 80? Add a max-width. Font under 15px? Increase it. That's usually all you need.

## Don't Make Me Squint

- Readability beats fancy.
- Five factors: size, line height, line length, contrast, letter spacing.
- Body text minimum: 16px, 1.6 line height, max 75 characters wide, 4.5:1 contrast.
- Never use all-caps for body text. Never go below 15px.
